text: Tucutí is a corregimiento in Chepigana District, Darién Province, Panama with a population of 1,200 as of 2010. Its population as of 1990 was 1,455; its population as of 2000 was 1,263. ==References== Category:Corregimientos of Darién Province Category:Road-inaccessible communities of Panama
title: Tucutí
